✅ 1️⃣ Make your fresh updated ZIP

In ~/myhearthub, run:

zip -r myglobalhearthub.zip . -x "*.zip" "*.log" "*.pid" "node_modules/*"

This will create a new myglobalhearthub.zip with:

All your updated files

Excluding .zip, logs, PIDs, and node_modules



---

✅ 2️⃣ Confirm it’s there

ls -lh myglobalhearthub.zip


---

✅ 3️⃣ Deploy

./deploy.sh


---

⚡ That’s it!

Your new version goes live — Node + MariaDB restart automatically.
If you like, I can also make a backup.sh so you always keep a copy before deploying.


